! openvms_dcl.pats
!
! OpenVMS DCL (Digital Command Language) syntax highlighting pattern for (X)NEdit
! by Oscar van Eijk <support@oveas.com>
!
! Dec.  1, 2005
! Feb. 18, 2025, let's finish what I started almost 20 years ago :)
!
!
! Configuring (X)NEdit to use a new pattern set: 
! 
! * Close your (X)NEdit sessions 
! * Start an (X)NEdit session using the import command line option with the pattern you downloaded: 
! 
!   # (x)nedit -import pats-file
! 
!   (replace pats-file with the correct file name) 
! * Go into the recognition patterns dialog (Preferences>Default Settings>Syntax Highlighting>Recognition Patterns...) and verify that the patterns are imported 
! * Use Preferences>Save Defaults... to store the modifications. 
! 
! This version has been verified with the following versions
!  - NEdit  5.5
!  - XNedit 1.5.3
!

